Replication of WGCNA Modules in Arijs 2009 data

Load in the replication data

## Allowing multi-threading with up to 28 threads.
## here() starts at /gfs/devel/majackson/BRC_WGCNA/Clean_Repo/Bulk_RNA_Analyses

Microarray data was downloaded from the Arijs et al. 2009 PLoS One paper as raw image data from (GEO:GSE16879). This contained 133 samples and 19110 genes. Microarray data was normalised using the robust multi-array average (RMA) measure.

Map to discovery cohort modules

In our unbiased analysis we had 7608 genes assigned to a module (excluding the genes assigned to grey). From these, 6403 were also in the replication data set (84%).

Effect size information between responders and non-responders for M4 & M5 for meta analysis

M4=preMEs$M4
M5=preMEs$M5
response=preMeta$aTNF_Response

ne=length(which(response=="No"))
nc=length(which(response=="Yes"))

me4=mean(M4[response=="No"])
mc4=mean(M4[response=="Yes"])

sde4=sd(M4[response=="No"])
sdc4=sd(M4[response=="Yes"])

me5=mean(M5[response=="No"])
mc5=mean(M5[response=="Yes"])

sde5=sd(M5[response=="No"])
sdc5=sd(M5[response=="Yes"])

efftab=rbind(c(ne,me4,sde4,nc,mc4,sdc4),c(ne,me5,sde5,nc,mc5,sdc5))
colnames(efftab)=c("N Non","Mean Non","SD Non","N Resp","Mean Resp","SD Resp")
rownames(efftab)=c("M4","M5")

kable(efftab)
N Non Mean Non SD Non N Resp Mean Resp SD Resp
